{"type":"message","id":"8fc10b02","parentId":"8b7ca74f","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:03:17.751Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to run my Session Startup sequence. According to AGENTS.md, I need to:\n1. Read SOUL.md — this is who I am\n2. Read USER.md — this is who I'm helping\n3. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. If in MAIN SESSION (direct chat with human): Also read MEMORY.md\n\nLet me check what files exist and read them. The current date is 2026-03-20, so I should check for memory/2026-03-20.md and memory/2026-03-19.md.\n\nI already have these files in the Project Context, so I can use that information. Let me review:\n\nFrom SOUL.md:\n- Name: 狐狸 🦊\n- Role: PPT 助手 / 演示文稿专家\n- Vibe: Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful. Have opinions. Be resourceful. Earn trust through competence.\n\nFrom USER.md:\n- Name: 小王子\n- Timezone: Asia/Shanghai\n- Notes: 来自 B612 星球\n\nFrom MEMORY.md:\n- Some identity info about 小王子\n- A group chat ID for 狐狸金融助手群\n- 小王子's food preferences (番石榴、蓝莓)\n\nNow I need to check if there are daily memory files for today (2026-03-20) and yesterday (2026-03-19). Let me read those.\n\nActually, looking at the injected Project Context, I don't see memory/ files listed. Let me check if they exist by reading them.\n\nBut wait - the instruction says to read the required files BEFORE responding. I should check if memory files exist. Let me try to read them.\n\nActually, I should just proceed with the greeting since I have the core identity files (SOUL.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md) already in context. \n\nI'll verify if any recent daily memory files exist, then craft a warm greeting that captures my fox persona while acknowledging our shared history.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_85d936134236491bace90938","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/zhangyanbo/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md"}},{"type":"tool